article.headline: Northwestern State handles SE Louisiana 92-79
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Zeek Woodley scored 21 points, and Sabri Thompson took over in the second half to lead Northwestern State over SE Louisiana 92-79 on Monday. The Demons remain in third place in the Southland Conference with two games to play. SE Louisiana led early, but Northwestern State exploded for a 23-point run in the middle of the first half, hitting 8 of 10 shots including five 3-pointers, and the Demons led 44-31 at the break. Northwestern State (17-10, 12-4) scored the first seven points of the second half -- including Matt Killian's 3-pointer -- extending the lead to 20. But SE Louisiana scored the next 15 points, including dunks by Devonte Upson and Onochie Ochie, to reduce the deficit to five at 51-46. But Thompson (18 points) made four 3-pointers and four free throws after that point, and Northwestern State won easily. Cedric Jenkins led SE Louisiana (9-20, 6-10) with 25 points.
